# Database And Supabase Safety

Use this rule only in projects that use Supabase or managed SQL schemas.

- Enable Row Level Security on all application tables.
- Add policies needed for features to function correctly; do not rely on permissive defaults.
- Do not connect to or mutate remote databases unless the user explicitly asks and approves the action.
- Prefer migration files for database changes, and tell the user what to apply manually when that is their workflow.
- If the project has `sql/setup.sql` or equivalent bootstrap SQL, keep it current with schema and policy changes.
- Do not hide missing database data with fallback records; surface the error clearly.
